  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different jurisdictions:\n\n1. United States Approach\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Comprehensive anti-money laundering (AML) regulations\n- Strict reporting requirements\n- Significant criminal and civil penalties\n- Emphasis on financial institution compliance\n\n2. European Union Approach\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directives (AMLD)\n- Harmonized regulatory framework\n- Enhanced customer due diligence\n- Risk-based supervision\n- Cross-border cooperation mechanisms\n\n3. United Kingdom Model\n- Proceeds of Crime Act\n- Financial intelligence unit (UKFIU)\n- Robust regulatory oversight\n- Focus on transparency and asset recovery\n- Strong international collaboration\n\n4. Swiss Approach\n- Historically more permissive\n- Strict banking secrecy laws\n- Gradual alignment with international standards\n- Enhanced transparency requirements\n- Sophisticated compliance frameworks\n\n5. Asian Jurisdictions\n- Varied approaches\n- Singapore: Strict regulatory environment\n- Hong Kong: Robust AML frameworks\n- China: Increasing regulatory sophistication\n\n6. Common Implementation Elements\n- Customer identification\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- International information sharing\n- Risk-based compliance strategies\n\nThis overview highlights diverse yet converging global approaches to combating money laundering.",
